search for &quot;Kumon&quot; in a good search engine (www.webcrawler.com) and have a look for anything by the Jumon foundation Inc. if you cant find anything email my address and i will try to find the direct website for you.<br>
<br>
Failing that you could get &quot;Japanese for busy people (The Kana version)&quot; it covers basic speech ideal for total beginers to advanced students. It does not use Romaji (Romanised japanese words) only Hirigana and Katakana, which means a solid understanding of both Kanas is learnt.<br>
<br>
Also i reccomend you get a English-Jap dictionary and a Jap-English dictionary that explains in Hriagana not kanji.<br>
